{"session_id":"svc-1778193899914470277","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-07T22:45:01.929709091Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-c2a66f45-20260507T224456-5a848f63","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260507T224456-5a848f63/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260507T224456-5a848f63/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260507T224456-5a848f63/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260507T224456-5a848f63/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260507T224456-5a848f63/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 2. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-c2a66f45\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ereview: block terminal review classes without no-progress accounting\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Pre-close review now prevents close on REQUEST_CHANGES and BLOCK, but terminal review classes are not first-class operator-blocking outcomes. Spec gaps, missing acceptance criteria, too-large-at-depth-cap, unsafe/out-of-scope changes, and exhausted review errors need to park the bead with needs_human metadata and must not consume no-progress budget.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_post_review.go:141-197 handles reviewer errors by appending review-error or review-manual-required events and setting review_malfunction, but it does not classify exhausted review errors into a stable operator-required stop class.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_post_review.go:233-277 records REQUEST_CHANGES/BLOCK and applies the generic review triage decision, but it does not map findings to review_spec_gap, review_missing_acceptance, review_too_large, or review_unsafe_or_out_of_scope classes.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1262-1275 can still apply no-progress cooldown logic after non-success outcomes unless those outcomes are separately suppressed.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1964-1987 has no terminal-review exclusion vocabulary.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add a review terminal classification helper for pre-close review outcomes.\u0026#xA;- Map review_spec_gap, review_missing_acceptance, review_too_large at depth cap, review_unsafe_or_out_of_scope, and exhausted review_error to blocked needs_human/operator-required metadata.\u0026#xA;- Ensure these terminal review classes append structured review/operator events, unclaim or park the bead consistently, and do not increment no-progress/no_changes budget.\u0026#xA;- Preserve the existing APPROVE close path and the existing malformed-review bounded retry behavior until the retry cap is exhausted.\u0026#xA;- Leave review_fixable_gap repair scheduling to the sibling repair bead.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not implement repair cycles in this bead.\u0026#xA;- Do not change reviewer prompt content except for any minimal schema labels needed by tests.\u0026#xA;- Do not change cost-cap behavior.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEPS\u0026#xA;Depends on ddx-89ab3fda for Blocked stop vocabulary and ddx-224ffcd2 for no-progress-ineligible review outcomes.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. A production review terminal classifier maps review_spec_gap, review_missing_acceptance, review_too_large at depth cap, review_unsafe_or_out_of_scope, and exhausted review_error into blocked needs_human/operator-required outcomes.\u0026#xA;2. TestReviewTerminalClassifications_BlockWithoutNoProgress covers all terminal classes and proves no no-progress/no_changes budget is incremented.\u0026#xA;3. TestReviewTerminalClassifications_ExhaustedReviewErrorNeedsHuman covers review_error retry exhaustion and the emitted review-manual-required/operator metadata.\u0026#xA;4. Existing TestBoundedReviewRetry_NthFailureEmitsManualRequired, TestPreCloseReview_RequestChangesPreventsClose, and TestPreCloseReview_BlockPreventsClose still pass.\u0026#xA;5. APPROVE review behavior remains unchanged: TestPreCloseReview_UnanimousApproveCloses still passes.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestReviewTerminalClassifications|TestBoundedReviewRetry|TestPreCloseReview\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... passes.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:10, area:agent, area:review, area:work, kind:fix, reliability, adr:024, spec:FEAT-010, split-from:ddx-9228a484\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-5cb6e6cd\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"8a315e2f9dad4dde374c06ce210ba8febf3df10d\" bundle=\".ddx/executi